      <p style="word-spacing: -1; line-height: 100%; margin-top: -1; margin-bottom: -1"><font size="4"><b><font face="Tahoma">The
      Evil One (Part three) -
      </font></b></font></p>
      <p style="word-spacing: -1; line-height: 100%; margin-top: -1; margin-bottom: -1"><font size="4"><b><font face="Tahoma"><br>
      </font></b></font><b><font size="4" face="Tahoma">Vengeance comes Calling</font></b></p>
            <p style="MARGIN: 0px; WORD-SPACING: 0px" align="left"><i>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>
            </i>
            *The scene: a dark chamber, barely lit by a few candles on skull bases. The air is ripe with                      the stench of decaying flesh and stagnant blood. A skeletal minion stands in a nearby                      alcove watching ever vigilantly for unwanted visitors. A dark elven male is within the                      chamber, floating a&nbsp;
      few inches off the ground as if he were some form of ghost. The Dark&nbsp;<br>
                      elf is busy at work unwrapping some type of bundle as the sounds of a child are heard                      crying suddenly....*<br>
      <br>
                      Quiet rodent... nau have time to hear dos cries this moon. Nau to worry though little                      woodchuck, dos fright will nau last too long.<br>
      <br>
                      *The dark elf continues to unwrap the bundled child until, at last, the pale naked form of a                      wood elven child is seen in the dim light. Barely visible on the child are welts that slowly                      ooze blood. The welts seeming deliberately drawn out into arcane designs on the child's                      skin. The Dark elf looks over the runic markings once again then nods approvingly.*<br>
      <br>
                      All seems in readiness.... Now little Vermin let udos test out this latest gift from Innoruuk.&nbsp;<br>
      <br>
                      *The Dark Elf grins evilly then draws forth an ornate dagger, it's wavy blade resembling a                      wisp of flame mounted onto a handle shaped from some lost souls bones. He takes the                      blade then slices the child's throat with one quick motion then chants rhythmically as the                      child's life's blood flows out of it's body. A moment later the chamber is silent. The Dark Elf                      lays the small corpse atop a nearby table then rings a bell. Out of an adjoining room, a                      ruckus is heard followed by moans of pain. A moment later, a dark elven priestess brings in                      a high elven priest in the tattered remains of ceremonial robes. The Dark elf speaks to the                      high elf*&nbsp;<br>
      <br>
                      Vendui again pasty, dos see here the broken form of one of dos treehugging kin. It is in                      dos powers to save its spirit, mend its flesh xas? Dos be a good lacky and heal this child.&nbsp;
      Usstann quite worried about it.<br>
      <br>
                      *The high elf looks up in defiance, but succumbs to what he knows was said as being                      truth... he must try to aid the boy despite his present company. He mutters a few curses                      and sighs as he sees wound to the throat and the tortuous carvings on the child's body.                      The High Elf speaks...*<br>
      <br>
                      I shall do what must be done for the child, though it pains this one to know it returns to                      this land to be in the presence of such filth such as your dark kind, but the Light bids me                      help the fallen one. Your times will come as well dark ones.<br>
      <br>
                      *An evil grin crosses the dark elves face and then he motions to the dead child. The high                      elf priest scowls at the dark elf and then steps forth, a tear in his eye as he sees the dead                      child. The high elven priest begins to pray to his god in hopes of reviving the poor child...                      moments pass and the priest continues to chant with a look of growing concern crosses                      the priests face. A few more moments pass and the high elven priest begins to sweat and                      mutters about something being wrong... all the while an evil smirk grows larger and larger                      upon the dark elf's face. The High Elf speaks...*<br>
      <br>
                      Wh.. wh..what have you done! The child's soul can not return to the flesh! The spirit doe                      snot reply to the lights call! This is impossible! You shall all Pay fo.... *CRACK*<br>
      <br>
                      *The sound of a splitting skull resounds in the chamber, as the high elven priest crumples                      onto the floor, blood flowing freely from a large wound on his skull. The Dark elven                      priestess stands nearby and nods to the other dark elf... a gore covered mace still held in                      her hand.*<br>
      <br>
                      Well then... it would seem that usstann's new magic is a success... dos try it dalninil... see                      it dos olath powers can bring this deadflesh back to life again.<br>
      <br>
                      *The dark elven priestess nods then begins her chant and ritual to resurrect the dead                      child. Beads of perspiration begin to cover the dark females skin as she tries repeatedly to                      raise the child's spirit again. The dark elven priestess lets out a long breath then shakes                      her head*<br>
      <br>
                      Ah... so neither dark nor light powers can alter the outcome of this little magic. Well now,                      perhaps usstann shall cause that little stuntee some stress yet. Lifebane nau forget, nau...                      nau forget anything ever.<br>
      <br>
                      *Lifebane turns to face a moaning noise and sees the high elf crawling slowly around on                      the floor of the chamber.*<br>
      <br>
                      Ah... dos nau dead yet priest? Good good. Usstann needs the practice.<br>
      <br>
                      *Lifebane kicks the fallen high elf in the head once knocking it back into unconsciousness.                      Lifebane quickly carves the runes onto the high elf's flesh as well. Once done, the same                      chant and ritual is performed and the high elf's throat cut as well. Lifebane smiles evilly                      then speaks to the priestess*<br>
      <br>
                      A good moon's work nau? 2 souls devoured by Innoruuk. Oh xas, now that usstann                      recalls... the stuntee.. xas, that one has a messenger, or
      was it the mongrel that sends                      the lizard.. nau matter, but usstan will
      need to keep tabs on that one. Hrrmmmm....<br>
      <br>
                      *Lifebane sees the nearby corpse of the child still on the table, he nods to himself then                      with one swipe of the dagger, cuts the abdomen of the child open. He reaches in with one                      dark hand and pulls out a handful of the child's innards. Lifebane eyes the innards closely,                      grunts a bit then nods as his face is again converted into an evil smirk.*<br>
      <br>
                      Seems the innards tell a tale of a lizard being eyes for others.. very well. Let the lizard                      watch. And let the rivvil listen to its rantings. Nau matter in the end.. That one will serve or                      fall sooner or later... so say the innards.&nbsp;<br>
      <br>
                      *Lifebane rings a nearby bell twice and the doors are opened up revealing 2 large brutish                      figures in the doorway. Kaglaaz and Garthud make quite adept guards at times such as                      these, or so Lifebane has noted.*<br>
      <br>
                      Dos two, take these carcasses to the cook Zukuku, let the brute prepare something good                      for udos to feast on.<br>
      <br>
                      *Lifebane watches as the trolls bicker over which corpse to carry and
      who will eat what                      parts. Lifebane chuckles as the trolls sample the
      "food" on their way out of the chamber.*<br>
      <br>
                      Now olath priestess, let udos go find some of the others and advise them of udos new                      trickery.<br>
      <br>
                      May Innoruuk save dos from the forces of Nerfromancy~~~&nbsp;<br>
                      Lifebane Lil'Valdruk<br>
                      Shadowclan Elder<br>
